      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "h3",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Extra Attack"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Starting at 5th level, you can attack twice, rather than once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "h3",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Arcane Jolt"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "At 9th level, you've learn new ways to channel arcane energy to harm or heal. When either you hit a target with a magic weapon attack or your steel defender hits a target, you can channel magical energy through the strike to create one of the following effects:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The target takes an extra 2d6 force damage."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Choose one creature or object you can see within 30 feet of the target. Healing energy flows into the chosen recipient, restoring 2d6 hit points to it."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can use this energy a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once), but you can do so no more than once on a turn. You regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "h3",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Improved Defender"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "At 15th level, your Arcane Jolt and steel defender become more powerful:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The extra damage and the healing of your Arcane Jolt both increase to 4d6."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Your steel defender gains a +2 bonus to Armor Class."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Whenever your steel defender uses its Deflect Attack, the attacker takes force damage equal to 1d4 + your Intelligence modifier."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
